.TH KEVIN 1 "2026-02-04" "Kevin Bot" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kevin \- helper commands for Kevin Bot (start, stop, status, log)
.SH SYNOPSIS
kevin-start
kevin-stop [--force]
kevin-status [ -t N | --tail N ] [ -v | --verbose ]
kevin-log [ -t N | --tail N ] [ -v | --verbose ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Kevin provides helper commands to manage the Kevin Discord bot on a local host. The commands are thin wrappers installed by the project's installer.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
kevin-start
Start the bot (equivalent to running the project's ./Scripts/run.sh helper).
.TP
kevin-stop [--force]
Stop the bot gracefully; use --force to send SIGKILL if needed.
.TP
kevin-status
Show whether the bot is running, list process IDs and uptime, and display the latest log location. Use -t/--tail to show last N lines and -v/--verbose for more output.
.TP
kevin-log
Wait for the bot to start (if necessary), then tail the active log file until the bot process exits. Use -t/--tail to begin with the last N lines and -v/--verbose for status messages.
.TP
Discord commands (available as prefix commands with `?` and as slash `/` commands):
.TP
?remind <time> <message> [--persistent]  — Set a reminder. Time examples: 5m, 2h, 1d.
.TP
?myreminders — List your active reminders.
.TP
?setrandominterval <seconds> — (admin) Set a fixed random message interval (min 5s).
.TP
?setrandomcount <n> — (admin) Set number of random messages per interval (1–10).
.TP
?randomauto on|off — (admin) Enable or disable automatic randomization.
.TP
?randomsettings — Show current random message settings.
.TP
?ping — Respond with pong and latency.
.TP
?roll NdM — Roll dice (e.g. `?roll 2d6`).
.TP
?quote — Send a random short quote.
.TP
?dm <member> <message> — (restricted) Send a DM to a member (see project configs).
.TP
?purge <n> — (mod) Delete recent messages in a channel.
.TP
?kick <member> [reason] — (mod) Kick a member.
.TP
?ban <member> [days] [reason] — (mod) Ban a member and optionally remove message history.
.TP
?mute <member> [minutes] — (mod) Add a muted role; optional auto-unmute.
.TP
?unmute <member> — (mod) Remove mute role.
.TP
?modset <subcommand> — View and set per-guild moderation settings (prefix, mod role, log/welcome channels).
.TP
?synccommands — (admin) Force-sync application (slash) commands with Discord.

These commands are also available as application (slash) commands (for example `/remind`, `/ping`, `/roll`, `/purge`, `/synccommands`) where supported by the server and Discord client.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start the bot
\fBkevin-start\fR
.TP
Stop it forcefully
\fBkevin-stop --force\fR
.TP
Show status and last 20 lines
\fBkevin-status -t 20\fR
.TP
Stream log until stop
\fBkevin-log -t 200\fR
.SH FILES
$HOME/Desktop/Kevin_Log_*.txt
$PROJECT_ROOT/kevin.env (local configuration file)
